 <h2 class="professional-title professional-title" class="professional-title">Our Heritage &amp; Origins</h2>
 <p class="professional-body">CSGA Global was founded on a simple but urgent premise: as AI systems become deeply embedded in critical infrastructure, governance cannot be an afterthought. It must be constitutional &mdash; principled, enforceable, and internationally portable.</p>
 <p class="professional-body">Born from the convergence of cybersecurity expertise and AI ethics research, the CSOAI Group set out to build not just another compliance checklist, but a living constitutional framework that bridges the gap between technical implementation and regulatory obligation across jurisdictions.</p>
 <p class="professional-body">Today, our 52-article constitutional framework &mdash; mapped to 17 international standards including ISO 42001, NIST AI RMF, the EU AI Act, and NATO STANAG protocols &mdash; serves as the foundation for organisations seeking responsible AI adoption at scale.</p>
 <p class="professional-body">From healthcare and financial services to defence and critical national infrastructure, CSGA Global provides the standards, platforms, certifications, and human expertise that make trustworthy AI a reality rather than an aspiration.</p>
